hopobject.body: How many weeks' holiday a year are there? l-arginine side effects thyroid Crows are often accused of “sickening, cruel attacks on newborn lambs, in which their eyes, tongues or navels are pecked out, often without killing them”. Predation is very seldom witnessed and most accounts are simply inferences based on the condition of a dead or injured animal. The only scientific account of 297 lamb deaths in Argyll showed that 48 per cent died of starvation, 22 per cent were stillborn, and nine per cent died of disease. Hooded crows had attacked 48 per cent of the lambs, but examination revealed that only 17 per cent were alive at the time.
